Teaching Experience


2019-2021

Teaching Assistant, ECE4534 Embedded System Design, Virginia Tech

Teaching assistant for ECE4534 embedded system design course for five consecutive semesters. This is a project-oriented design course focused on developing a robotic system utilizing microcontrollers and various sensors. In this role, I led Q&A sessions, held office hours, and evaluated student homework, while also serving as a mentor for the design groups. My contributions were instrumental in helping students to acquire a deep understanding of the course material and successfully complete their projects.

My contributions proved to be a key factor in helping students excel in the course.
